                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16333216" author="cziegeler" created="Sat, 20 Jan 2018 15:19:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The code currently uses the component context (impl) to get the service registration for updating the properties. However, if the component is not instantiated yet, there is no component context. Therefore getting the service registration fails and the service properties are not updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16333226" author="cziegeler" created="Sat, 20 Jan 2018 15:45:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in the R7 branch with rev 1821750 in the R6 with rev 1821754&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately with this change, the behaviour for components returning service properties in activate change as the MutablePropertiesTest#test_mutable_properties_consumer fails. With this change, the service properties are updated earlier now which I guess makes that test fail as the service properties returned by activate happen later. I&apos;ve no clear idea how this work, so I leave the old behaviour (bug) for components in the proprietary felix namespace as is.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
